    <title>Galois (sub)Groups</title>
    <introduction permid="MCb">
      <p permid="JHv">
        Consider the polynomial <m>a(x) = x^4 - 2</m> in <m>\Q[x]</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>

    <exercise workspace="15%" permid="sJk">
      <statement>
        <p permid="pOE">
          Find the splitting field <m>E</m> for <m>a(x)</m> over <m>\Q</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution permid="leL">
        <p permid="dAm">
          There are four roots of <m>a(x)</m>, namely <m>\pm \sqrt[4]{2}</m> and <m>\pm\sqrt[4]{2}i</m>.
        </p>
      </solution>
    </exercise>

